WEBVTT

00:08.157 --> 00:11.693
Simply put, this
combination of elements could allow us

00:11.695 --> 00:14.296
to cyberform entire worlds.

00:15.204 --> 00:18.460
Why do I feel a
Shockwave plan coming on?

00:19.840 --> 00:22.670
Do not think for a moment,
Starscream, that it has gone

00:22.673 --> 00:25.440
unnoticed that you left me
at the mercy of the Autobots.

00:25.442 --> 00:30.512
Master? Are you going to allow
one Lieutenant to harm another?

00:33.249 --> 00:36.952
- Master?
- I'm thinking.

00:40.324 --> 00:45.260
I am tempted to force you to
share my perception of things.

00:45.262 --> 00:50.732
No! I only did what I thought
was best for the mission,

00:50.734 --> 00:54.770
but I do feel compelled to
add that it was my very error

00:54.772 --> 00:58.507
in judgment that made this
happy accident possible!

01:00.577 --> 01:04.745
If I recollect, you were
seeking to purge your laboratory

01:04.748 --> 01:07.482
of sensitive materials
before the Autobots arrived,

01:07.484 --> 01:09.284
were you not?

01:09.286 --> 01:13.012
Your argument... is logical.

01:17.261 --> 01:20.862
Exemplary teamwork.
Now tell me, Shockwave,

01:20.864 --> 01:24.800
why does this cyber-matter
resemble chaos?

01:24.802 --> 01:28.270
The basic elements are
apparently unstable...

01:28.272 --> 01:30.772
I will turn my attention
to correcting that.

01:32.576 --> 01:36.712
Nevertheless, should we use
this cyber-matter to restore

01:36.714 --> 01:39.581
Cybertron, or cyberform Earth,

01:39.583 --> 01:43.418
we would require a launch
mechanism, would we not?

01:43.420 --> 01:47.923
<i>Then we will focus
all our remaining resources</i>

01:47.925 --> 01:52.527
<i>upon the successful reconstruction
of the Omega lock.</i>

01:59.681 --> 02:02.217
<i>sync & correction by f1nc0
Resync by Metal Warrior | addic7ed.com </i>

